The paper deals with the problem of object localization in images, which is a key problem in computer vision. The proposed method uses Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and gradient weights to discover discriminative regions for object localization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for weakly supervised object localization, which involves training a model with only image-level class labels. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on several datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
